div1.p:
In the District Court at Seattle
In the matter of the application of William Warden for discharge upon writ of Habeas Corpus Special Return of Sheriff
And said comes the Sheriff of King County John H. McGraw and for the rturn to the writ of Habeas Corpus herein responds and returns

That said William Warden or alais Ross is held by Respondent upon a warrant foregiving the petitioner with a felony to wit. Burglary and that the houses issued his confinement upon said charge had not expired and the said petitioner has not yet had a before the Justice commiting him, the time for said examination not having arrived and expened, and respondent says no further Respondent having no knowledge or imformation sufficient to form any official as to the matters alleged in

Matters of fraud conspiracy or confederation, and therefore retrieves nothing as to the same, and for another return to say respecfully in comitted convict Respondent makes his applicant respectfully hereto attactched especially apart. Sheriff of and of County John H. McGraw Subscribed and sworn this 11 day of May A D 1889 R. M. Hopkins Clerk.
